                            <comment id="258997" author="simmonsja" created="Sat, 30 Nov 2019 17:27:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is a good idea. Its not just issues with naming but times when similar functionality is duplicated elsewhere that the new name doesn&apos;t sync with the older names which causes problems. We saw that with the&#160;qos_threshold_rr work. For the linux client at one time we had a&#160;sysfs-fs-lustre that listed the sysfs files we had as well as document what they did. Perhaps we could add this to the OpenSFS tree. It have to be updated. This file could be used for verifying if the parameter names are right. I attached the original file but it needs an update.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
